        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 6:12AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 612 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairview, or near Cleveland, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
McLarty, Alabama International Dragway, Walnut Grove, Easley, Rainbow
City, Mountainboro, Rockledge, Altoona, Cleveland, Rosa, Fairview,
Aurora, Oneonta, Attalla, Allgood, Ramsey, Susan Moore, Nectar, Big
Wills Creek, and Chamblees Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
